+++</md></sn><sn><md>## Present Continuous Tense{.text-center}

&gt; **Structure:** Subject + am/is/are + v-ing + ext <br>
&gt; **Use:** Actions happening right now or temporary actions <br>
&gt; **ব্যবহার:** এখন চলছে এমন কাজ বা সাময়িক কাজ বোঝাতে ব্যবহৃত হয়।

#### Fact
* The only tense that describe current action.
* am/is/are represent person whereas
* v-ing denote time
* Not all v-ing is any continuous tense it must have helping verb(am/is/are/was/were/etc)
---

+++ story

Suppose one of your friends visits your house, and you ask him:

####  “What are you doing?”

He replies:

#### **"I am drinking tea."**

Here’s what it means:

* He is `currently drinking tea` at that moment.
* This sentence describes an action that is happening `right now`.
* For actions occurring at the moment of speaking, we use **Present Continuous Tense**.

&gt; **Note:** If he had said **"I drink tea"**, it would mean he `usually drinks tea` or prefers tea in general — which is Present Simple.
+++

