</md></sn><sn><md>### Present Perfect Continuous{.text-center}

&gt; **Structure:** Subject + has/have + been + $v-ing$ + ext <br>
&gt; **Use:** Action `started` in the past and `still continuing` <br>
&gt; **বাংলায় ব্যবহার:** কোনো কাজ অতীতে `শুরু হয়ে এখনো চলছে`।

#### Fact
* Both present perfect and present perfect continuous action started in the past but
* Present perfect `end` and result exist in the present and
* Present perfect continuous action `continue or just end` now

---
+++ story
Suppose one of your friends visit your house and you were outside of your house.So your mom told him to wait and give him a cup of tea.On arriving you ask him -

#### “What have you been doing?”

He replies:

#### **"I have been drinking tea."**

Here’s what it means:

* He started drinking tea **some time ago** and is **still drinking it now**, or **just finished** drinking it.
* This sentence describes an action that **began in the past** and has been **continuing up to the present**.
* For actions that started earlier and are still going on (or have just recently stopped), we use **Present Perfect Continuous Tense**.

&gt; **Note:**
&gt; If he had said **"I have drunk tea"**, it would mean he **already finished** drinking tea — which is **Present Perfect Tense**.
&gt; But **"I have been drinking tea"** emphasizes the **duration or continuity** of the action until now.
+++
---
+++ Example

| উদাহরণ                                                | ব্যাখ্যা (কেন Present Perfect Continuous)    | বাংলা অর্থ                              |
| ----------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| 1. I `have been reading` for two hours.                 | দুই ঘণ্টা ধরে পড়ছি → অতীত থেকে এখন পর্যন্ত। | আমি দুই ঘণ্টা ধরে পড়ছি।                |
