#### Key Difference

| Aspect      | Past Perfect                             | Past Perfect Continuous                                  |
| ----------- | ---------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Form**    | had + past participle (V₃)               | had been + V-ing                                         |
| **Focus**   | Completion of the action                 | Duration or continuity of the action                     |
| **Example** | I had drunk tea before I came.           | I had been drinking tea before I came.                   |
| **Meaning** | He `finished` drinking tea, then came. | He `was in the middle of drinking` tea before he came. |

---

#### Summary

* **Past Perfect** → Emphasizes `what happened first` (completed action).
* **Past Perfect Continuous** → Emphasizes `how long` or `how continuously` the first action was happening before another past action.

