* It `emphasizes both **duration** and **completion**`  up to a specific point in the future**.

&gt; I will have been drinking tea for 10 minutes before you arrive.

**Explanation:**
This means that **by the time you arrive tomorrow**, he `will already have spent 10 minutes drinking tea`, showing the **continuity and duration** of the action before the next future event occurs.

