&gt; This shows his **daily habit** or **routine** — something that happens regularly.

---

#### **2. Present Continuous Tense**

&gt; **Arif is studying for his exams now.** <br>
&gt; This shows an action that is **happening at the moment of speaking**.

---

#### **3. Present Perfect Tense**

&gt; **Arif has finished two chapters.** <br>
&gt; The action is **completed**, but the **result** (two chapters done) is still **relevant now**.

---

#### **4. Present Perfect Continuous Tense**

&gt; **Arif has been studying for three hours.** <br>
&gt; This emphasizes the **duration** of an action that **started earlier** and is **still continuing**.

Event started in the past and continue in present.Both present prefect and present prefect continuous started in the past,but in prefect the action already competed but in present perfect continuous the action still continue.

---

#### **5. Past Simple Tense**

&gt; **Arif studied very hard last night.** <br>
&gt; This shows a **finished action** that happened at a **specific past time**.

---

#### **6. Past Continuous Tense**

&gt; **Arif was studying when his friend called him.** <br>
&gt; This means his **studying** was **in progress**, and the phone call **interrupted** that action.

---

#### **7. Past Perfect Tense**

&gt; **Arif had studied before he went to bed.** <br>
&gt; This indicates that **studying happened first**, and **sleeping happened later** — one past action before another.Emphasizes the `completion` of earlier event. 

---

#### **8. Past Perfect Continuous Tense**

&gt; **Arif had been studying for hours before he went to bed.** <br>
&gt; This highlights the **ongoing duration** of studying that **continued for some time** before he finally went to bed.Emphasizes `continuity` of earlier event..

---

#### **9. Future Simple Tense**

&gt; **Arif will study tomorrow morning.** <br>
&gt; This shows a **future plan or decision** to study.

---

#### **10. Future Continuous Tense**

&gt; **Arif will be studying at 8 a.m. tomorrow.** <br>
&gt; This indicates an action that **will be in progress** at a **specific future time**.

---

#### **11. Future Perfect Tense**

&gt; **Arif will have studied all chapters before the exam starts.** <br>
&gt; This expresses that his studying will be **completed before** another future action (**the exam**).Emphasizes the `completion`. 

---

#### **12. Future Perfect Continuous Tense**

&gt; **Arif will have been studying for five hours before the exam starts.** <br>
&gt; This emphasizes the `duration` of the studying — it will **continue up to** a particular future time (**the exam**).

